Job Description:
Sr. Bank Business Systems Specialist

First Century Bank has an exciting career opportunity available for a Sr. Bank Business Systems Specialist to join our team. The Bank is planning to implement a new enterprise-wide software, and this would be the initial project to be supported by this position.

This individual will analyze and manage business requirements throughout the enterprise-wide software implementation team. They will facilitate and support requirements workshops, business process modeling, writing detailed functional specifications for new and changed complex information systems, preparing test cases and testing strategies, conducting peer reviews to ensure 'as-built' information systems conform to specifications, and ensure that processes are followed. All steps must be documented effectively, and clearly. Additionally, this individual will participate in the analysis of business requirements and recommend effective, efficient, flexible technical solutions to meet business needs. This person will perform work within the full range of project development methodologies, which could include Waterfall and Agile methods.

First Century Bank has specialized in providing financial services through technology channels for our clients. The Sr. Business Systems Analyst is a career opportunity which would facilitate the smooth implementation of the enterprise software, as well as be involved in future programs to be implemented at the Bank.

Duties will include the following:

Prepare the assessment of current systems and interdependencies including conducting operations assessment and documenting current procedures and systems;
Define and create written functional and technical specifications that meet business needs;
Documenting system requirements based on processing volumes and other software interfaces;
Review system dependencies to ensure all are addressed as a part of the conversion, ensuring that all system integration touch points are identified;
Communicate effectively with all team members, stakeholders and project sponsors on technical and non-technical processes;
Lead and facilitate group tasks across all levels of the organization to deliver anticipated outcomes;
Develop elements of systems design, including scoping documents, user stories, business process documentation, workflow charts, diagrams, data migration rules, business rules, wireframes, or other detailed deliverables;
Continually optimize processes using technology to solve issues, increase efficiency, and add to the bottom line;
Achieve core business competencies in rapidly changing environments by using innovative technology;
Work with the Software QA team and end-users to create comprehensive test cases, plans and strategy;
Collaborate with end users and developers on developing comprehensive test cases;

· Assist in the development of training material. Conduct training and organization change management as appropriate.

· Understand issues and resolve them through data analysis, technical research and team collaboration on highly complex issues.

· Enhance the end user experience by providing actionable information;

Facilitate user acceptance testing and perform integration testing, as required;
Keep the end user/customer at the forefront of thought; support, guide, influence users to see opportunities and value with new approaches using technology;
Assist users with realizing their strategy and goals through the use of new technology;

· Performs such other duties as may be assigned or which inherently or logically belong with the position.

· Exemplify FCB's values while carrying out its mission and organizational goals and priorities.

This position is a hybrid position whereby the individual will be able to work remotely and also come into the office as needed for training and to build camaraderie with other team members.

Qualified candidates should possess a bachelor’s or master’s degree in Information Systems or Business Management Systems and 5+ years of related experience, or combination of education and experience and 5+ years of related. Individual should be proficient in Microsoft products, Critical thinking and Problem Solving, File and Data processing. Ideal candidates would have experience with the Jack Henry Silverlake product. Individual should also have a general understanding of relational databases, scripting, and workflows. Candidates should possess a high level of attention to detail, exceptional communication skills, project management skills and business analysis skills. Critical thinking, including the ability to approach problems logically and make informed decisions based on data is also required.

